               <history>
                  <summary>
                     <origPlace xml:lang="en">Northern India</origPlace>
                     <date calendar="#gregorian" notBefore="1500" notAfter="1700">Between 1500 and 1700</date>
                  </summary>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Formerly belonged to John Bardoe Elliott (1785-1863) of Calcutta. Owner’s description of work and contents ff.i-iv. p.619 bears the note ‘Read at Patna June 1825 J.B.E’. Fly-leaf bears signature J.B. Elliott.</p>
                     <p>The manuscript may be one of the two sent from India by Elliott before 1847 to the scholar<persName type="standard"
                                  ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/#Bland,_Nathaniel,_1803-1865"
                                  key="person_20108923">Nathaniel Bland (1803-1865)</persName>. The manuscript was certainly in Bland’s collection of oriental manuscripts which was sold through Bernard Quaritch in 1866 to<persName type="standard"
                                  ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/#Crawford,_Alexander_Crawford_Lindsay,_Earl_of,_1812-1880"
                                  key="person_97751058">Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford</persName>.</p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Purchased by Mrs Enriqueta Rylands, on behalf of the John Rylands Library, in<date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date>from<persName type="standard"
                                  ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/#Crawford,_James_Ludovic_Lindsay,_Earl_of,_1847-1913"
                                  key="person_9985420">James Ludovic Lindsay, 26th Earl of Crawford</persName>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
